&TUTORIAL ------------------ ASM2 BACK UP UTILITY --------------------- TUTORIAL
&NEXT SELECTION ===>%SELECT                             &
$
&                     ------------------------------------
                      | QUEUEING DATASETS TO BE RESTORED |
                      ------------------------------------
$
  DATASETS ARE QUEUED FOR RELOADING BY SELECTING OPTION&R$ON THE&ASM2 BACK UP
  UTILITY$MENU.  THE NAME OF THE DATASET TO BE RELOADED IS ENTERED IN
  THE&NAME$FIELD. NORMAL TSO NAMING CONVENTIONS APPLY.  FULLY QUALIFIED DATASET
  NAMES MUST BE ENCLOSED IN SINGLE QUOTES&(')$.

  IF MULTIPLE BACK UP VERSIONS EXIST,  AND YOU DO NOT WANT TO RELOAD THE LATEST
  VERSION,  YOU MAY SPECIFY THE RELATIVE VERSION IN MUCH THE SAME WAY AS
  GENERATION DATASETS. YOU SPECIFY THE NEXT TO LATEST VERSION BY ADDING&(-1)$
  FOLLOWING THE NAME. &(-2)$SPECIFIES THE ONE BEFORE THAT,  AND SO ON.

  WHEN THE BATCH RELOAD JOB IS COMPLETE,  A MESSAGE WILL BE SENT TO THE TSO
  USER WHO REQUESTED THE RELOAD.

